@mheon @dfr PTAL
I think this should simplify things and allow more code sharing between linux and bsd.

WIP because I need to change a dependency in c/common

> I like it. Good change to simplify things. I do suspect this won't help terribly much with the missing/bad NS errors beyond moving where they happen, though.

Yes although moving them will hopefully make it more obvious where to root cause is. And actually I think the replaceNetNS function had a bug that might caused this. It checks:
```
if ctr.ensureState(define.ContainerStateRunning, define.ContainerStatePaused) {
	return fmt.Errorf("joining network namespace of container %s: %w", ctr.ID(), err)
}
```

This is wrong because it used the old state and  thus compared against the container state, it would need to use the newState instead which was just read from the db.
